caption: Food was spectacular. Great service friendly and outdoor seating. Love it!

Enzo’s is my favorite restaurant in the Bronx.  We live about an hour away and make sure we go at least 3 times a year. The meatball appetizer with onions and long hots is delicious. Now .. I never order chicken or veal out.. about 6 years ago we came here for the first time.  I tried the veal parmigiana and was absolutely blown away.  This dish melts in your mouth.  The veal is beyond tender.  I can’t vouch for anything else because I only order the veal parmigiana for dinner.  Desserts are awesome too!!  Service is always great, tonight we had Artie as our waiter.  He was fantastic.  Everyone there is extremely friendly.  Update ....., Went back last night.. 3/27 with our friends. We ordered a few different items.  The polenta with sausage was very, very good.  The calamari was good but could be a bit crispier. Salad with goat cheese, walnuts and pears was very flavorful.  The gnocchi’s were little pillows of heaven.  Light and delicious. Stuffed chicken breast was excellent. Veal chop parmigiana (pounded down) was melt in your mouth tender.  Love this place!!  It’s worth the hour ride.
Food was great amazing services

So Paquales was closed and I desided to go to Enzos for the first time as I heard they had prety good food. I assure you I was very disappointed. I got the calamari which was good but very small portioned for the highest price I’ve ever seen calamari in my life. Not to mention no parsley ,salt , or pepper. Then I got the pork ossubocco and boy that was very flavorless I had to dump a bunch of garlic oil on top of it. Aswell we got cavatelli which looked so machine made and the spinach ngochi and that was just discusting. Will not be returning . The staff was very nice and attentive but the food just wasn’t up to par, especially for a bunch of Italians that love food and don’t care what the cost is .

The stuffed peppers were mainly rice, not enough meat, the mac and cheese was very mild white mac and cheese. Disappointing haul, we tried stuffed peppers, meatballs, mac and cheese, eggplant rollatini, chicken marsala, beef barley soup and pasta fagioli soup.  The chicken was very good, the rest tasted fine however was not something we'd seek out again.  I recommend Mike's Deli or Mario's.

He said, he wasn’t going to put a 2nd heater on because it was just the two of us. Hey Google Review. Here's the sound off on ENZO's located at the bite of Arthur Ave. From exceptional service and highest regards going towards Nesto and Reuben to the outstanding taste of their House special Calamari and finally honorably mentioning their delicious Cannoli, I present to you this must stop Shop if you visit the BX's Lil Italy. My mother and I had the pleasure of a visit on a Friday afternoon about 3pm. We ordered as stated the calamari with a accompanying app in the Eggplant Rollatini. There are no few words that could do justice to the presentation, the taste, the overall after thought. I believe a picture is worth a thousand words and with that said, please see below. Other than that we also ordered the Salmon Dijon and the roasted pork panini. The salmon was moist and flaky, I know, a contradiction but never the less a reality and much worth the addition to any lovers of salmon on the planet. As for the panini, my only critique was that I found it too dry and too doughy. It needed a zesty sauce and as luck would have it, I borrowed some from the salmon's honey mustard sauce and was satisfied BUT I think it needs a creamy light cheese sauce to match to perfection. Overall, service and taste bring this destination Foodscape to a echoing MANGIA. Buon Appetito

(Translated by Google) I was in Enzo's on August 23 of the current year, I came to the place by references from a blog about New York where he was mentioned as one of the best in Little Italy (Bronx). Also check the score on Google And as it was good we decided to go. We chose to eat a plate of ravioli and a Veal parmigiana (veal with parmesan) that came with spaghettis and cost $ 24. When they bring us the dish, we noticed that the Spaghettis were missing, so we claimed it and they brought them later. In addition we also asked the waiter for the Veal because the color was so clear that we thought it was chicken and he told us that we noticed that it was not because it had a different bone than this. At the time of receiving the bill, to our surprise, we found that the value of the Veal was $ 42 (the letter contained a single value, that of $ 24), we thought it was a mistake and we called the waiter, who So far he had been very kind, and he told us that that was the value because the veal came with bone and that he had warned us twice, which is totally false because at no time did he show us the existence of that difference in the Price referring only to bone to explain that it was beef and not chicken (it should be noted that the waiter was Latin and spoke perfectly Spanish so there is no misunderstanding here under the language). The waiter ends up assuming that it was his mistake because he had been the one who asked for that bone dish in the kitchen, goes to speak with the person in charge of the place to fix the account and returns saying that there will be no change because we had already I ate the dish, so we asked to speak with her, who was all the time near the table where we were but it took me more than 10 minutes to come to resolve the issue. When he finally decided to approach, the first thing he told us was that the dish we had eaten the same knowing that he had bone, to which I try to explain (in English because the lady did not speak Spanish and did not worry about calling the waiter who had attended us to be able to clearly translate what we were trying to tell her) that nobody had told us that the dish was more expensive for having bone to which she replied that she understood that nobody had told me but that she had eaten it anyway (an inconsistency), To which I replied that we had eaten it precisely because we did not know about that price difference, which is worth clarifying, IT WAS ALSO FOUND IN THE LETTER, to which it responds to me in a very superb way that although the waiter had not told us anything we should know that in all parts of the world the value with bone was more expensive, to which I stated that that was not the case, and that we had chosen the dish for the value that appeared in the letter and we didn't have more than that to be able to pay, so after a long time of discussion, and very reluctantly, the lady ended up fixing the value in the account, telling us that the waiter who had attended to us was going to pay for what What he had done. In short, they wanted to charge us a value that did not appear anywhere in the account with the excuse that we had eaten it and that we should know in advance that the price of bone-in meat was higher because it is worldwide, a maneuver clearly deceiving !!!! I WOULD NOT RETURN OR RECOMMEND IT!  (Original) Estuve en Enzo's el día 23 de Agosto del año en curso, llegué al lugar por referencias de un blog sobre Nueva York en donde se lo mencionaba como uno de los mejores de Little Italy (Bronx). Además verifique la puntuación en Google y como era buena decidimos ir. Elegimos para comer un plato de ravioles y una Veal parmigiana (ternera con parmesano) que venía con spaghettis y costaba 24 dólares. Cuando nos traen el plato notamos que faltaban los spaghettis por lo que lo reclamamos y los trajeron luego. Además también le preguntamos al mozo por la Veal porque el color era tan claro que creímos que era pollo y nos dijo que notaramos que no lo era ya que tenía un hueso diferente al de este. Al momento de recibir la cuenta, para nuestra sorpresa, nos encontramos con que el valor de la Veal era de $42 (en la carta figuraba un único valor, el de $24), creímos que se trataba de un error y llamamos al mozo, quien hasta el momento había sido muy amable, y nos dijo que ese era el valor porque la ternera venía con hueso y que él nos lo había avisado dos veces, lo que es totalmente falso porque en ningún momento nos manifestó la existencia de esa diferencia en el precio haciendo solo referencia al hueso para explicarnos que se trataba de ternera y no de pollo (cabe destacar que el mozo era latino y hablaba perfectamente español por lo que no existe aquí ningún desentendimiento en virtud del idioma). El mozo termina por asumir que fue su error porque había sido el quién pidió en la cocina ese plato con hueso, se dirige a hablar con la encargada del lugar para que arregle la cuenta y regresa diciendo que no va a haber ningún cambio porque ya habíamos comido el plato, por lo que pedimos hablar con ella, quién estuvo todo el tiempo cerca de la mesa donde nos encontrabamos pero tardo más de 10 minutos en venir a resolver la cuestión. Cuando por fin decidió acercarse, lo primero que nos dijo fue que el plato lo habíamos comido igual sabiendo que tenía hueso, a lo que intento explicarle (en inglés porque la señora no hablaba castellano y tampoco se preocupó por llamar al mozo que nos había atendido para poder traducir claramente lo que intentábamos decirle) que nadie nos había dicho que el plato era más caro por tener hueso a lo que me responde que ella entendía que nadie me lo hubiera dicho pero que de todas formas lo había comido (una incoherencia), a lo que le respondo que lo habíamos comido justamente porque no sabíamos de esa diferencia de precio, que vale aclarar TAMPOCO SE ENCONTRABA EN LA CARTA, a lo que me responde de manera muy soberbia que a pesar de que el mozo no nos había dicho nada deberíamos saber que en todos lados del mundo el valor con hueso era más caro, ante lo que la manifesté que eso no era así, y que nosotros habíamos elegido el plato por el valor que figuraba en la carta y no teníamos más que eso para poder pagar, por lo que después de un largo rato de discusión, y de muy mala gana, la señora terminó por arreglar el valor en la cuenta, manifestandonos que el mozo que nos había atendido iba a pagar por lo que habia hecho. En definitiva, quisieron cobrarnos un valor que no figuraba en ningún lugar de la cuenta con la excusa de que lo habíamos comido y que debíamos saber de antemano que el precio de la carne con hueso era más alto porque así lo es en todo el mundo, una maniobra claramente engañosa!!!!. NO VOLVERÍA NI LO RECOMIENDO!

Felt price was fair. Went on Mother's Day at noon, when it opened. Got busy around 1:30.

It took a very long time to get the 2 glasses of wine we ordered and staff though theatrical in reading the specials to us kind of lost interest after our meal was ordered.   But nothing can erase the first question our 2nd waiter asked a woman at our table.  Totally inappropriate and very poor judgement.  Enough so we will not return again.  Our experience was told to the manager on duty
